PHP7 Server setup
Like my first server setup file, I'm still new to doing this so use this at own risk. All information I've just compiled searching the net.

--Update and upgrade Ubuntu--
sudo apt-get update
sudo apt-get upgrade -y
sudo apt-get dist-upgrade -y
sudo apt-get autoremove -y

--Apache install--
sudo apt-get install apache2 -y
sudo apt-get install apache2-utils -y
sudo service apache2 restart

--Misc--
sudo apt-get install -y language-pack-en-base
sudo apt-get install python-software-properties
sudo apt-get update

--PHP7 install--
sudo add-apt-repository ppa:ondrej/php
sudo apt-get update
sudo apt-get install -y php7.0
*sudo apt-get install php7.0-cli
sudo apt-get install php7.0-fpm
sudo apt-get install php7.0-gd
*sudo apt-get install php7.0-json
sudo apt-get install php7.0-mysql
*sudo apt-get install php7.0-readline
*sudo apt-get install libapache2-mod-php7.0
sudo apt-get install php7.0-curl
sudo apt-get install php7.0-mcrypt
*sudo apt-get install php7.0-opcache
sudo apt-get install php-ssh2
sudo apt-get install php-zip
sudo apt-get install php-http
sudo apt-get install php7.0-xml

* All of these messaged that they were already the newest version and didn't appear to be required
in the installation. I use a apt-get autoremove at end which gets rid of anything extra they install
that is no longer required.

--Drupal enables--
sudo phpenmod -v 7.0 mcrypt
sudo a2enmod rewrite headers
sudo service apache2 restart

--MySQL install--
sudo apt-get install mysql-server-5.6
sudo mysql_secure_installation
sudo service mysql restart

--Update, upgrade and reboot--
// This probably isn't necessary but I figure it can't hurt.
// I include because on my second access to server the
// system told me there were upgrades available and a system reboot required.
sudo apt-get update
sudo apt-get upgrade -y
sudo apt-get dist-upgrade -y
sudo apt-get autoremove -y
sudo reboot

Good luck.
